"1328":"1328","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruński, kujawsko-pomorskie, Polen"},"nl":{"1 April 1276–30 March 1336":"1 april 1276–30 maart 1336","1276–1336":"1276–1336","1288–1328":"1288–1328","1327–1410":"1327–1410","1224–1293":"1224–1293","1236–1276":"1236–1276","30 March 1336":"30 maart 1336","1 April 1336":"1 april 1336","1275":"1275","1293":"1293","1 April 1276":"1 april 1276","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1236":"1236","1 January 1327":"1 januari 1327","1224":"1224","1410":"1410","1288":"1288","1276":"1276","11 June 1276":"11 juni 1276","30 December 1293":"30 december 1293","10 September 1328":"10 september 1328","1328":"1328","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruński, kujawsko-pomorskie, Polen"},"en":{"1 April 1276–30 March 1336":"1 April 1276–30 March 1336","1276–1336":"1276–1336","1288–1328":"1288–1328","1327–1410":"1327–1410","1224–1293":"1224–1293","1236–1276":"1236–1276","30 March 1336":"30 March 1336","1 April 1336":"1 April 1336","1275":"1275","1293":"1293","1 April 1276":"1 April 1276","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1236":"1236","1 January 1327":"1 January 1327","1224":"1224","1410":"1410","1288":"1288","1276":"1276","11 June 1276":"11 June 1276","30 December 1293":"30 December 1293","10 September 1328":"10 September 1328","1328":"1328","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Torun","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Hanoch, Moshe, Shira.","Dutch (also <b>Van Toren</b>): topographic name from Middle Dutch <i>tor(r)en</i> ‘tower’ (from Latin <i>turris</i>), or a habitational name from any of many places called with this word.","Swedish (<b>Torén</b>): ornamental name from the personal name <i>Tor(e)</i> (see   Thor  ) + the adjectival suffix <i>-én</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>-enius</i> ‘relating to’."],"variants":[{"name":"Thor","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Erland, Eyvind, Nels.  Southeast Asian Chor, Tong, Chia, Chu, Kong, Seng, Tou, Chee, Ching, Chou, Chue, Eng, Thai, Moua, Neng, Pao, Yeng, Yer, Blong, Chong, Choua, Houa, Shoua, Soua.","Swedish and Danish: from a short form of any of various Scandinavian personal names containing the first element <i>Thor</i> (Old Norse <i>Thórr</i>), the name of the god of thunder in Scandinavian mythology.","English: from the Anglo-Scandinavian name <i>Thōr</i>, <i>Thūr</i>, probably short forms of Old Norse compound names in <i>Thór-</i>, <i>Thúr-</i> (see 1 above)."]}]},{"name":"Nicholaus","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the post-classical Greek personal name <i>Nikolaos</i>, derived from <i>nikē</i> ‘victory’ + <i>laos</i> ‘people’. The spelling with <i>-ch-</i> first occurred as early as the 12th century, and became firmly established at the time of the Reformation, although  <b>Nicolas</b>  is still occasionally found.  St Nicholas  was a 4th-century bishop of Myra in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Nicholaus Torun was born on 1 April 1276, his father, Stefanos Torun, was 52 and his mother, Guarda Saxon, was 40. He married Ursula Saxon in 1315, in Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 30 March 1336, at the age of 59, and was buried in Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland."},"et":{"1 April 1276–30 March 1336":"1. aprill 1276–30. märts 1336","1276–1336":"1276–1336","1288–1328":"1288–1328","1327–1410":"1327–1410","1224–1293":"1224–1293","1236–1276":"1236–1276","30 March 1336":"30. märts 1336","1 April 1336":"1. aprill 1336","1275":"1275","1293":"1293","1 April 1276":"1. aprill 1276","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1236":"1236","1 January 1327":"1. jaanuar 1327","1224":"1224","1410":"1410","1288":"1288","1276":"1276","11 June 1276":"11. juuni 1276","30 December 1293":"30. detsember 1293","10 September 1328":"10. september 1328","1328":"1328","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruński, kujawsko-pomorskie, Poola"},"fi":{"1 April 1276–30 March 1336":"1. huhtikuuta 1276–30. maaliskuuta 1336","1276–1336":"1276–1336","1288–1328":"1288–1328","1327–1410":"1327–1410","1224–1293":"1224–1293","1236–1276":"1236–1276","30 March 1336":"30. maaliskuuta 1336","1 April 1336":"1. huhtikuuta 1336","1275":"1275","1293":"1293","1 April 1276":"1. huhtikuuta 1276","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1236":"1236","1 January 1327":"1. tammikuuta 1327","1224":"1224","1410":"1410","1288":"1288","1276":"1276","11 June 1276":"11. kesäkuuta 1276","30 December 1293":"30. joulukuuta 1293","10 September 1328":"10. syyskuuta 1328","1328":"1328","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruński, kujawsko-pomorskie, Puola"},"fr":{"1 April 1276–30 March 1336":"1 avril 1276–30 mars 1336","1276–1336":"1276–1336","1288–1328":"1288–1328","1327–1410":"1327–1410","1224–1293":"1224–1293","1236–1276":"1236–1276","30 March 1336":"30 mars 1336","1 April 1336":"1 avril 1336","1275":"1275","1293":"1293","1 April 1276":"1 avril 1276","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1236":"1236","1 January 1327":"1 janvier 1327","1224":"1224","1410":"1410","1288":"1288","1276":"1276","11 June 1276":"11 juin 1276","30 December 1293":"30 décembre 1293","10 Septembe